  • public class X2NumericValue
extends X2Value
    Restriction of the XMCDA Value type to single numeric values of type: integer, real, rational and NA.

    Java class for numericValue complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="numericValue">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.decision-deck.org/2012/XMCDA-2.2.1}value">
       <sequence>
         <element name="description" type="{http://www.decision-deck.org/2012/XMCDA-2.2.1}description" minOccurs="0"/>
         <choice>
           <element name="integer" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}int"/>
           <element name="real" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}float"/>
           <element name="rational" type="{http://www.decision-deck.org/2012/XMCDA-2.2.1}rational"/>
           <element name="NA" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string"/>
         </choice>
       </sequence>
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>
